@startuml TASFA_Fast_Link_Strategy

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderThickness 2
skinparam BoxBorderThickness 2
skinparam MaxMessageSize 120
hide footbox

actor "Browser Client" as Client
participant "TASFA JS\nDownload Scheduler" as JS
participant "Service Worker" as SW
participant "Media Player\n<video>/<audio>" as Player

box "TASFA Server" #F8F8F8
    participant "Handshake API" as Handshake
    participant "Chunk API" as ChunkAPI
    participant "Direct Download\nRange API" as RangeAPI
end box

== Link Classification ==

Client -> JS: read navigator.connection

alt downlink >= 900\nsaveData off\nRTT <= 80ms or unknown\neffectiveType not 2g/3g
    JS -> JS: classify as 1000M-class candidate
    JS -> Handshake: GET /.../handshake\nchunk_size=64MiB\nlink_downlink_mbps, link_rtt_ms,\nlink_effective_type, link_save_data
else downlink >= 500 with same stable hints
    JS -> JS: classify as 500M-class candidate
    JS -> Handshake: GET /.../handshake\nchunk_size=48MiB\nlink_downlink_mbps, link_rtt_ms,\nlink_effective_type, link_save_data
else 100M-class or unstable / unknown quality
    JS -> JS: keep normal TASFA strategy
    JS -> Handshake: GET /.../handshake\nchunk_size=stored preference\nnormal link hints
end

Handshake -> Handshake: validate fast-link hints server-side

alt Qualified fast link
    Handshake --> JS: session with chunk_size <= 48MiB or 64MiB
else Not qualified
    Handshake --> JS: session with normal chunk_size <= 32MiB
end

== Scheduler Policy ==

alt fast-link large video/audio
    JS -> JS: cap maxParallel\n desktop <= 4, mobile <= 3
    JS -> JS: force coalesce/span = 1
    JS -> JS: progressive fetch limit\n desktop <= 3, mobile <= 2
    JS -> JS: shallow forward window
else 100M-class or non-media
    JS -> JS: use existing adaptive TASFA policy
    JS -> JS: normal chunk growth, span growth,\nand media parallel floors
end

== Media Transfer ==

alt Native Range playback
    JS -> SW: TASFA_SESSION\nsession_id, token, fast-link flag
    Client -> Player: set src = direct media URL
    Player -> SW: Range request
    SW -> RangeAPI: Range + X-TASFA-Session-ID/Token
    RangeAPI --> SW: 206 Partial Content
    SW --> Player: 206 Partial Content
else Progressive TASFA media
    JS -> SW: TASFA_STREAM_OPEN
    loop bounded near-future window
        JS -> ChunkAPI: GET .../chunk/:index\nspan=1
        ChunkAPI --> JS: one large chunk
        JS -> SW: TASFA_STREAM_CHUNK
    end
    SW --> Player: ordered bytes
end

== Runtime Demotion ==

loop successful chunk samples
    JS -> JS: compute observed Mbps EWMA
end

alt 1000M-class large media\nand early EWMA < 250 Mbps
    JS -> JS: demote session to normal strategy
    JS -> JS: restore standard maxParallel,\ntargetParallel, coalesce, span
else 500M-class large media\nand early EWMA < 150 Mbps
    JS -> JS: demote session to normal strategy
    JS -> JS: restore standard maxParallel,\ntargetParallel, coalesce, span
else Actual throughput is healthy
    JS -> JS: keep 64MiB + low parallel policy
end

== Service Worker Guardrail ==

Player -> SW: Range request
SW -> RangeAPI: authenticated Range fetch

alt Server returns 206
    RangeAPI --> SW: 206 Partial Content
    SW --> Player: 206
else Server returns non-206 and fast-link flag is set
    RangeAPI --> SW: 200 or other response
    SW --> Player: forward response without full Blob slicing
else Normal session fallback
    RangeAPI --> SW: 200 response
    SW -> SW: legacy cache/blob range slicing
    SW --> Player: fallback response
end

note over JS,SW
FAST prefers fewer large transfers on true 500M+ links.
Unstable wireless or poor observed throughput falls back to
the normal 100M-class TASFA strategy.
end note

@enduml
